A convicted murderer who failed to return to prison after unescorted leave in Glasgow has been arrested.
James Lieser, 38, did not return to HMP Greenock on 24 April and was last seen in Parkhead, Glasgow, that day.
Lieser was convicted in 2004 of murdering Steven Collins and had served 11 years of a 12-year sentence before he absconded.
Police Scotland expressed their thanks to the public for information leading to his arrest.
